# Incident Response — Preparation

> TCM Security course notes — the Preparation phase is the foundation of every effective incident response program. Everything you do (or fail to do) before an incident occurs directly determines how well you can respond when one happens.

**Reference documents:**
- **SANS Security Forms** — [https://www.sans.org/media/security-training/mgt512/secinc_forms.pdf](https://www.sans.org/media/security-training/mgt512/secinc_forms.pdf)
- **NIST SP 800-84** (Testing IR Plans) — [https://nvlpubs.nist.gov/nistpubs/Legacy/SP/nistspecialpublication800-84.pdf](https://nvlpubs.nist.gov/nistpubs/Legacy/SP/nistspecialpublication800-84.pdf)
