## Summary

| Area | Key Preparation Activity |
|------|-------------------------|
| End Users | Awareness training, phishing simulations, reporting channels |
| Stakeholders | Define roles for IT, Legal, PR, Data Owners before an incident |
| Communications | Contact lists, escalation protocols, out-of-band channels |
| Physical | War room, secure evidence storage (CIA) |
| Tracking | TheHive or ticketing system with access/version control |
| Hardware/Software | Forensic workstation, jump kit, clean removable media |
| Asset Management | Full inventory: OS, apps, IPs, criticality, network diagrams |
| Exercises | Tabletops, Backdoors & Breaches, NIST SP 800-84 |
| IR Plan | Playbooks (what/when) + Runbooks (how) |
| Notifications | Pre-approved policies for law enforcement, legal, regulators, insurance |
| Documentation | Document everything, slow down, chain of custody |
